{
  "id": "smallhold-4xr",
  "title": "Phase 4: Posting and Delivery",
  "description": "Implement post creation, deletion, and outbound federation. This is the v0.1 release milestone — after this phase you can post from a real client and your followers on mastodon.social see the post. The delivery worker is in-process, polls the delivery_queue table, and handles retry with exponential backoff and per-domain circuit breaking.",
  "design": "Delivery retry schedule: 1m, 5m, 30m, 2h, 8h, 24h, max 6 attempts then dead_at. 410 Gone → dead immediately. 4xx (non-410) → dead after 1 retry. Circuit breaker: per-domain, 10 consecutive failures → 1hr backoff in-memory. Idempotency: hash key + account_id, 24h TTL, prune in background task. Content rendering: pulldown-cmark for markdown, ammonia for HTML sanitization, mention linking on @user@domain patterns.",
  "acceptance_criteria": "Post from Ivory → followers on mastodon.social see it in their home timeline within 60s; delete the post → followers see deletion; Idempotency-Key prevents duplicate posts on retry; delivery worker retries on 5xx, marks dead on 410, circuit-breaks after 10 consecutive domain failures",
